title.narrative: Eliminating TB in Indonesia

description.narrative: Indonesia - Tuberculosis - Directorate General of Disease Prevention and Control, Ministry of Health of The Republic of Indonesia - MOH. This program has the following goals: To reduce TB related morbidity and mortality in thirty four provinces of Indonesia, with strong contribution of health and community systems. To halt and reduce drug resistant TB incidence among new TB cases at community. To reduce TB/HIV related mortality. The objectives of this program are: To achieve universal access to prevention of TB infection and care, support, and treatment of TB for key affected populations at higher risk, people living with HIV and general population through TB program leaderships strengthening at national and sub-national level. Increase detection and notification of all forms of TB From 129/100,000 pop in 2015 to 240/100,000 pop by 2020. Ensure treatment success of 90% for drug-sensitive TB treatment in NTP and non NTP providers by 2020.. Ensure universal access to diagnosis and treatment for drug-resistant TB by 2020 (55% of estimated MDR cases are diagnosed & treated by 2020 and 80% by 2025)
